        <article>
            <h2>ollier masonry</h2>

            <dl>
                <dt>Project type:</dt>
                <dd>Private mobile app</dd>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

                <dt>Plaform:</dt>
                <dd>iOS</dd>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

                <dt>Stack:</dt>
                <dd>Javascript/HTML on Cordova, NodeJS and Postgres on Heroku</dd>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

                <dt>Contributions:</dt>
                <dd>End-to-end design, development and distribution</dd>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

                <dt>Challenge:</dt>
                <dd>Masonry company needed to be able to manage workforce of more than 60 employees at many job sites. Previously, this work was handled by a single individual on paper.</dd>
                <div class="clearfix"></div>

            </dl>

            <h3>Summary:</h3>
            <p>The app and service allow for several supervisors to log in to create jobs, assign workers to those jobs, and track resources including time and automated job site reports. Non-privileged employees can view the app, to see when they are scheduled to work, at which job, and who with. The app is distributed in a closed system via the Apple Enterprise program.</p>

            <p>Office administrators can log in to a web-based reporting page, where they can review timesheets for a given job/employee as well as review daily job reports. This serves as a historical record of work performed and any issues encountered.</p>
        </article>

    </section>

